WEBVTT

00:06.089 --> 00:08.299
[REO Speedwagon playing
"Time for Me to Fly"]

00:09.926 --> 00:12.721
<i>♪ I've been around for you ♪</i>

00:12.804 --> 00:15.432
<i>♪ Been up and down for you ♪</i>

00:15.515 --> 00:17.892
<i>♪ But I just can't get any relief ♪</i>

00:17.976 --> 00:20.061
-[clapping]
-[dog barking]

00:21.354 --> 00:23.148
<i>♪ I've swallowed my pride... ♪</i>

00:23.231 --> 00:25.900
-[Wendy] Good boy!
<i>-</i>[panting]

00:25.984 --> 00:26.943
[toy squeaks]

00:27.027 --> 00:30.989
<i>♪ But you still make me feel</i>
<i>Like a thief ♪</i>

00:32.282 --> 00:35.869
<i>♪ You got me stealin' your love away ♪</i>

00:35.952 --> 00:38.204
<i>♪ 'Cause you never give it... ♪</i>

00:38.288 --> 00:41.750
Who's the best boy?
Who's the best boy?

00:41.875 --> 00:44.169
<i>♪ And we can't relive it ♪</i>

00:44.836 --> 00:50.300
[singing along] <i>♪ Oh, I make you laugh</i>
<i>And you make me cry ♪</i>

00:51.259 --> 00:58.224
<i>♪ I believe it's time for me to fly ♪</i>

00:58.308 --> 01:01.061
<i>♪ Time for me to fly ♪</i>

01:01.144 --> 01:04.230
<i>♪ Oh, I've got to set myself free</i> ♪

01:04.314 --> 01:06.566
<i>♪ Time for me to fly ♪</i>

01:06.941 --> 01:11.154
<i>♪ And that's just how it's got to be ♪</i>

01:12.197 --> 01:14.866
<i>♪ I know it hurts to say goodbye ♪</i>

01:15.450 --> 01:22.373
<i>♪ But it's time for me to fly ♪</i>

01:35.428 --> 01:36.304
Wendy?

01:48.149 --> 01:49.484
What are you doing?

01:53.363 --> 01:55.031
[gunshots]

01:58.326 --> 02:02.163
<i>♪ Oh, don't you know</i>
<i>It's time for me to fly ♪</i>

02:02.455 --> 02:06.584
<i>-♪ Oh, I've got to set myself free ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Time for me to fly ♪</i>

02:06.668 --> 02:12.215
<i>♪ Oh, baby, that's just how</i>
<i>It's got to be ♪</i>

02:13.216 --> 02:14.217
[soft moan]

02:20.640 --> 02:22.642
[snoring]

02:24.185 --> 02:26.187
[theme music playing]

02:39.701 --> 02:41.369
[Marty]
<i>Did you sleep all right last night?</i>

02:43.288 --> 02:44.205
[Wendy] Mm-hmm.

02:46.082 --> 02:47.250
You're, um...

02:47.333 --> 02:51.421
you're going to negotiate the hotel
at the new casino today, right?

02:52.964 --> 02:54.090
Helen's going with.

02:55.925 --> 02:57.343
You need any help with that?

03:00.930 --> 03:02.056
You know, actually...

03:02.640 --> 03:07.353
it'd be a huge help if you could deal with
the REO Speedwagon people-- person.

03:07.729 --> 03:08.897
His name's Dickey.

03:11.941 --> 03:13.026
Well, that's a shame.

03:14.652 --> 03:16.404
You know, last night...

03:17.739 --> 03:19.490
you yelled while you were sleeping.

03:21.576 --> 03:22.535
What?

03:22.952 --> 03:25.288
Uh, you yelled, "I can't."

03:30.126 --> 03:31.002
Oh.

03:42.639 --> 03:43.765
[Wendy] How is your ex?

03:44.891 --> 03:46.392
Is he still in the hospital?

03:46.517 --> 03:49.938
He is,
and doing about as well as he should be.

03:51.147 --> 03:52.482
How are you and Marty?

03:53.816 --> 03:56.236
We're okay. We're-- We're good.

03:56.361 --> 03:57.570
We're just...

03:58.238 --> 03:59.948
We're a little disconnected at the moment.

04:00.031 --> 04:02.367
Ah. Same thing happened to us.

04:02.742 --> 04:05.536
When I started
eclipsing him professionally,

04:05.662 --> 04:08.081
he was no longer interested
in me sexually.

04:08.539 --> 04:10.541
Oh, I'd hardly say I'm eclipsing him.

04:10.625 --> 04:14.420
-Oh, please!
-No, we can't do any of this without him.

04:15.630 --> 04:18.299
Few people get my client's attention
the way you have.

04:22.845 --> 04:24.347
And should I be worried about that?

04:24.764 --> 04:26.432
-What, his attention?
-Mm-hmm.

04:27.225 --> 04:28.643
Only if you fuck up.

04:38.069 --> 04:41.072
There she is. Ugly as we left her.

04:42.740 --> 04:43.992
[Wendy] No one will be fired.

04:44.284 --> 04:48.204
In fact, you will continue to be paid,
and when you come back,

04:48.288 --> 04:52.875
you'll return to a more sophisticated
and healthier work environment.

04:53.751 --> 04:56.921
Good conditions, good pay,
and good benefits.

04:57.005 --> 04:59.048
[Anita]
What the hell do you think you're doing?

05:00.675 --> 05:02.510
These are promises.

05:03.219 --> 05:05.179
And I do not break my promises.

05:05.263 --> 05:08.516
We are addressing our workers
in our casino.

05:08.599 --> 05:10.560
You're closing it down.

05:10.643 --> 05:15.398
Well, we had an agreement in principle
to purchase the casino and hotel,

05:15.481 --> 05:16.607
and you reneged on the hotel.

05:16.691 --> 05:19.652
If you could all help me
and gather your things and safely...

05:20.236 --> 05:22.488
make your way off the boat. Thank you.

05:22.572 --> 05:25.074
It was a verbal agreement.

05:26.075 --> 05:27.744
Well, nevertheless, here we are.

05:27.827 --> 05:30.788
We have no use for a casino with no hotel.

05:30.955 --> 05:34.375
And you have no use for a hotel
with no casino.

05:34.500 --> 05:38.671
You'll lose a fortune if you shut down,
especially during the summer months.

05:39.255 --> 05:41.924
Hmm. We can afford that.

05:43.217 --> 05:45.053
-Can't we, Helen?
-Oh, yes, yes, we can.

05:45.136 --> 05:46.512
-We can afford that.
-Hmm.

05:47.347 --> 05:50.600
We are bigger than you, and we are meaner.
And we do not lose.

05:50.850 --> 05:52.393
So... [sighs]

05:52.643 --> 05:54.479
...why don't you just sell us the hotel?

05:55.438 --> 05:56.606
Have done with it.

06:01.986 --> 06:04.030
Oh. Mmm.

06:04.781 --> 06:05.990
[inhales deeply]

06:06.074 --> 06:09.327
-I'm so sorry you feel that way. Hmm.
-Hmm. Hmm.

06:40.608 --> 06:42.193
[knock on door]

06:45.947 --> 06:46.781
Hi.

06:48.825 --> 06:49.659
Hi.

06:51.828 --> 06:53.621
If I'm gonna spend
a lot of time someplace,

06:53.704 --> 06:55.373
might as well make it feel like home.

06:56.624 --> 06:59.961
This is Jeff. [sighs]

07:00.420 --> 07:01.671
And this...

07:04.715 --> 07:05.591
is me.

07:07.093 --> 07:08.344
Agent Maya Miller.

07:09.470 --> 07:10.430
Marty Byrde.

07:10.513 --> 07:12.390
So, show me around the place.

07:12.473 --> 07:14.475
-[patrons chattering]
-[machines chiming]

07:16.352 --> 07:18.646
You should come
to the REO Speedwagon show.

07:18.729 --> 07:20.773
[Maya] Well, I'll buy a ticket.
I like REO.

07:21.232 --> 07:24.402
REO, ELO, REM,

07:24.861 --> 07:25.945
MIA...

07:26.571 --> 07:27.613
TLC.

07:29.323 --> 07:32.952
So, let me explain this thing to you
for full transparency.

07:33.077 --> 07:35.705
I have a team of forensic accountants
deployed at the tables,

07:35.788 --> 07:38.624
creating a rough estimate
of your physical chip counts.

07:39.167 --> 07:40.293
NWA.

07:41.419 --> 07:42.295
[Marty] Mm-hmm.

07:42.378 --> 07:45.006
[Maya] Now, we'll compare those counts
to your receipts every hour

07:45.089 --> 07:46.507
and also check your cash boxes.

07:47.175 --> 07:49.886
You're trying to apply
Benford's Law of Large Numbers

07:49.969 --> 07:52.013
to create a predictable pattern?

07:52.638 --> 07:54.765
Helps us highlight any irregularities.

07:54.891 --> 07:57.268
Yeah, except that you're setting
a false baseline.

07:57.351 --> 07:59.645
You know, the mere fact that
you and your agents are here

07:59.729 --> 08:02.940
is gonna drive down my business, you know?

08:03.524 --> 08:07.653
I allow a margin of error of 3%.
That sound reasonable?

08:08.738 --> 08:11.115
Promise I'll be
as unobtrusive as possible.

08:11.199 --> 08:12.450
But I need hard data.

08:13.075 --> 08:15.369
If we leave and there's suddenly
a massive jump in revenue,

08:15.453 --> 08:17.246
well, that's cause for a new warrant.

08:18.289 --> 08:21.542
-We start this dance all over again.
-Hmm.

08:23.669 --> 08:24.545
May I?

08:27.256 --> 08:28.132
Yeah.

08:30.676 --> 08:31.719
[card reader beeps]

08:43.523 --> 08:46.692
Hey. Um... So, uh, that, uh...

08:47.527 --> 08:49.612
The new FBI agent, she's good.

08:49.695 --> 08:52.406
I don't know how we're gonna be able
to move money through here.

08:52.490 --> 08:55.660
Hmm. That's what you wanna tell me?

08:55.743 --> 08:57.286
That's why you called me up here?

08:58.246 --> 09:00.831
Well, also,
I should not have yelled at you

09:00.915 --> 09:03.167
for, um... helping out Wendy.

09:03.543 --> 09:04.460
Yeah, no shit.

09:04.585 --> 09:07.046
Yeah, I was outta the loop.
Things were moving fast.

09:07.129 --> 09:09.632
I'm not your fucking marriage counselor.

09:10.299 --> 09:12.760
-I'm trying to apologize.
-Okay.

09:18.391 --> 09:19.225
Well?

09:20.309 --> 09:22.270
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

09:22.979 --> 09:24.564
Okay? Let's move on.

09:24.689 --> 09:26.857
I need you to get Frank Jr. and his guys

09:26.941 --> 09:29.235
to smurf this week's run
into the new casino.

09:30.027 --> 09:32.321
Wendy says the new place
is supposed to be clean.

09:32.530 --> 09:33.823
She doesn't need to know.

09:34.448 --> 09:37.118
So, you're moving money in the new casino

09:37.201 --> 09:40.162
and you're asking me
not to tell your wife?

09:41.497 --> 09:42.540
In a nutshell.

09:42.623 --> 09:43.833
[Ben] We interrupting?

09:45.042 --> 09:47.420
[Marty] No, unh-unh, not at all.

09:47.753 --> 09:49.630
We just came for the boat keys.

09:50.172 --> 09:51.257
[Marty] Oh, yeah.

09:51.799 --> 09:53.050
I like this color on you.

09:55.553 --> 09:56.429
Gray?

09:57.179 --> 09:58.889
I was thinking we should hang out.

10:01.559 --> 10:02.893
You're joking me, right?

10:03.227 --> 10:04.395
Deadly serious.

10:04.937 --> 10:06.606
So, uh, you guys have a good time.

10:06.689 --> 10:07.982
Please, thank you.

10:08.065 --> 10:09.775
And safe would be great.

10:10.860 --> 10:11.777
Think about it.

10:16.073 --> 10:17.408
He's fucking weird.

10:17.950 --> 10:18.784
Yes, he is.

10:19.160 --> 10:22.079
Uh, do you think you can move 250?

10:23.831 --> 10:24.790
Yeah.

10:25.625 --> 10:27.585
With, uh, five or six guys...

10:28.753 --> 10:30.838
-it won't be a problem.
-Great, thank you.

10:45.645 --> 10:46.520
Fuck.

10:50.608 --> 10:53.903
[chattering, laughing]

11:20.554 --> 11:22.223
[cell phone ringing]

11:25.893 --> 11:26.727
Hey, Ruth.

11:27.228 --> 11:29.772
Great fucking job communicating
with your wife.

11:29.855 --> 11:31.691
She closed the fucking casino.

11:34.402 --> 11:36.112
Hmm? What are you talking about?

11:36.195 --> 11:39.198
The place is fucking deserted
and chained up.

11:40.783 --> 11:41.742
Marty.

11:41.909 --> 11:43.994
-Hey, Dickey Elston.
-Hey, Dickey.

11:44.078 --> 11:46.038
So, the rider, huh? For the band?

11:47.540 --> 11:51.544
Um, Ruth, let me talk to you
when you get here, please.

11:52.503 --> 11:55.297
Just get your fucking shit together,
Marty.

11:58.634 --> 12:00.886
Let me take a quick look at this, Dickey.

12:00.970 --> 12:02.805
Yeah, it's just the basics.

12:02.888 --> 12:06.517
Fiji, charcuterie, Xanax, crudité, oolong.

12:07.476 --> 12:08.894
[laughing] I'm kidding, man.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.313
Oh. Good.

12:11.772 --> 12:13.065
[Dickey] About the oolong.

12:13.774 --> 12:16.402
-[Marty] Hmm.
-Hmm. [laughs]

12:27.121 --> 12:29.540
[Charlotte] Dad just sent this over.
It's the band's rider.

12:31.751 --> 12:34.628
Don't forget, you have your appointment
with Mrs. Shelby today.

12:37.548 --> 12:39.967
[door opens, shuts]

12:40.050 --> 12:41.594
Well, this can't be good.

12:45.931 --> 12:46.932
Uh, your husband around?

12:48.350 --> 12:49.351
He is not.

12:50.144 --> 12:51.479
Yeah. You'll have to do then.

12:54.064 --> 12:55.941
Frank, you remember
my daughter Charlotte?

12:56.400 --> 12:57.651
-[Charlotte] Hi.
-Ah.

12:58.444 --> 13:00.905
Uh, you shut down the new casino.

13:01.363 --> 13:03.240
We're supposed to start the routes
this week.

13:04.658 --> 13:05.701
I'm sorry?

13:06.911 --> 13:07.787
Uh...

13:08.454 --> 13:10.831
We didn't do... [sighs]

13:10.915 --> 13:11.999
...what we did...

13:13.834 --> 13:15.127
out of charity.

13:20.549 --> 13:21.634
[Frank sighs]

13:23.093 --> 13:25.429
Would you mind getting me a cup of coffee
or something?

13:29.934 --> 13:30.893
[Charlotte] Sure.

13:36.816 --> 13:37.983
Why do I get the feeling

13:38.067 --> 13:40.236
you have absolutely no idea
what I'm talking about?

13:40.319 --> 13:41.153
Because I don't.

13:41.237 --> 13:43.280
-Then you better talk to your husband.
-Yes, I will.

13:47.243 --> 13:48.285
For the month.

13:49.954 --> 13:51.372
At the new rate...

13:52.456 --> 13:54.917
negotiated for the Missouri Belle.

13:58.337 --> 13:59.338
If you don't mind,

14:00.422 --> 14:02.508
how did you know the casino was closed?

14:03.509 --> 14:05.803
The blonde. Curly Sue.

14:06.846 --> 14:08.889
She had my boy's crew over there.

14:09.014 --> 14:10.891
Something about moving money.

14:18.315 --> 14:19.358
From now on...

14:20.317 --> 14:22.069
you'll be dealing with me on this.

14:27.199 --> 14:28.075
I don't care.

14:29.743 --> 14:31.161
As long as the checks clear.

14:36.750 --> 14:39.295
[door opens, shuts]

14:44.633 --> 14:46.135
[Marty] <i>I'm just asking for your help.</i>

14:46.218 --> 14:47.344
[Wendy] Actually, you're not.

14:47.428 --> 14:48.888
You're going behind my back

14:48.971 --> 14:53.017
to expressly do what you know
we are not allowed to do.

14:53.100 --> 14:54.518
Because you won't help.

14:54.602 --> 14:56.812
Do you not see a pattern here?

14:56.937 --> 14:59.690
You've done nothing but fight me on this.

14:59.815 --> 15:01.817
And now, now you want unfettered access

15:01.901 --> 15:04.737
to the very thing you've tried
to undermine since the very beginning.

15:04.820 --> 15:07.364
I don't want-- I <i>need</i> access, Wendy.

15:07.489 --> 15:08.490
We need access.

15:08.574 --> 15:11.869
We have made promises
to our shareholders about this casino,

15:11.952 --> 15:15.122
and I don't think-- I don't think we want
to annoy our shareholders.

15:15.205 --> 15:16.790
What would you have me do?

15:17.166 --> 15:19.543
[Wendy] I don't feel very compelled
to help you right now.

15:19.627 --> 15:22.296
I just had a very interesting conversation
with Frank.

15:24.048 --> 15:25.090
From Kansas City.

15:25.174 --> 15:26.133
Oh, yeah?

15:26.800 --> 15:27.676
Hmm.

15:28.552 --> 15:29.762
And you do...

15:30.220 --> 15:31.931
you do realize

15:32.014 --> 15:35.142
what a magnificently stupid

15:35.225 --> 15:39.063
and dangerous thing it was that you did
in Kansas, right?

15:39.897 --> 15:42.024
I pleaded with you, "Please don't do this.

15:42.149 --> 15:44.860
Please do not get us further in on this."
Remember that?

15:44.944 --> 15:46.695
Yeah. And because you didn't
get your way,

15:46.779 --> 15:48.322
you went behind my back to sabotage me.

15:48.405 --> 15:51.659
I was trying to protect our family, Wendy.
That's it.

15:51.742 --> 15:52.701
That is such--

15:52.785 --> 15:54.870
That is such a tired...

15:55.079 --> 15:57.206
-Is it? Okay.
-...tired excuse.

15:57.289 --> 16:00.668
Yeah. You know what you like to do?
You like to control your family.

16:00.751 --> 16:03.879
I'm asking you for fucking help
on a problem that you created,

16:03.963 --> 16:05.172
and you're not helping.

16:05.297 --> 16:06.882
That's the whole story.

16:07.466 --> 16:08.509
To you.

16:09.843 --> 16:11.929
-[sighs]
-[Sue] Let's pause there.

16:12.221 --> 16:14.223
-[stammers] Marty.
-Yeah.

16:14.306 --> 16:17.101
What would it look like
to achieve your objectives

16:17.184 --> 16:20.521
without interfering with Wendy's project?

16:22.231 --> 16:24.233
I think that that would look like death.

16:25.442 --> 16:27.361
[Sue] But what would it really look like?

16:29.321 --> 16:30.948
-Really death.
-[Sue] Okay.

16:31.824 --> 16:34.451
Marty, my mother had a saying.

16:35.160 --> 16:38.747
"Just like a pie is only
as good as its crust,

16:39.331 --> 16:43.419
a marriage is only as good as its trust."

16:43.877 --> 16:46.505
Going behind Wendy's back

16:46.588 --> 16:50.342
on a project that
is obviously meaningful to her

16:50.426 --> 16:52.386
violates that trust.

16:52.511 --> 16:54.513
Wendy is a powerful woman,

16:55.014 --> 16:58.559
and it's your responsibility
to nurture that, Marty.

16:59.143 --> 17:00.894
Not stifle it.

17:07.443 --> 17:11.280
What the hell was that? Hey, Sue!
What the hell was that?

17:12.448 --> 17:14.575
You told me to let her win a couple.

17:15.242 --> 17:16.452
Small things.

17:16.910 --> 17:19.371
-Small.
-I thought she was right.

17:19.455 --> 17:20.706
I don't give a fuck.

17:21.623 --> 17:23.083
You're yelling at me.

17:23.167 --> 17:24.918
Well, I'm angry, okay?

17:25.002 --> 17:28.172
Yes, Marty, you are.

17:28.338 --> 17:30.966
There is something deeper at play here.

17:31.425 --> 17:35.137
And I believe that you and Wendy
can be happy...

17:35.429 --> 17:37.431
if you let me help you.

17:37.514 --> 17:39.808
Save it. I'm not bribing you
to make us happy.

17:41.769 --> 17:44.438
[door opens, closes]

18:00.037 --> 18:03.082
So, uh... [clears throat]
...what did everyone do today?

18:07.294 --> 18:08.921
Okay... [clears throat]

18:09.213 --> 18:10.255
I'll start.

18:11.381 --> 18:14.468
Jonah took me to the caves.

18:15.928 --> 18:17.304
He jumped in the water.

18:17.888 --> 18:19.681
You let him jump in cave water?

18:19.765 --> 18:21.475
Who's gonna stop me?

18:21.558 --> 18:23.310
-[Jonah scoffs]
-[Charlotte] Well, how was it?

18:24.186 --> 18:27.940
It was not good.
It was very scary and disgusting.

18:28.023 --> 18:30.067
-[Charlotte] Mm-hmm.
-[cell phone ringing]

18:30.150 --> 18:31.652
Anybody know any jokes?

18:32.778 --> 18:33.862
I should get this.

18:34.363 --> 18:35.781
[Ben] Saved by the bell.

18:38.367 --> 18:39.785
Lucky bastard.

18:43.205 --> 18:44.164
Hello?

18:45.124 --> 18:46.416
[Navarro] <i>I'm interrupting.</i>

18:48.544 --> 18:49.878
No, no, not at all.

18:49.962 --> 18:52.840
<i>Yes, yes, I'm interrupting your dinner.</i>

18:53.465 --> 18:57.052
But not that I'm spying on you
or anything, it's just...

18:57.594 --> 19:00.055
it is, uh-- it's dinnertime there, no?

19:02.516 --> 19:03.600
[laughs] Yes.

19:04.017 --> 19:05.894
[laughs] <i>Did you cook?</i>

19:06.895 --> 19:07.813
Yes.

19:08.522 --> 19:10.524
<i>-Good.</i>
-[both laugh]

19:10.607 --> 19:11.650
<i>What did you make?</i>

19:11.775 --> 19:12.776
Chicken.

19:14.069 --> 19:16.363
Chicken roasted with vegetables.

19:17.698 --> 19:20.200
Well, I imagine you are pretty good
in the kitchen, no?

19:21.451 --> 19:22.494
[chuckles]

19:25.038 --> 19:26.832
We are very close on the hotel.

19:28.917 --> 19:31.879
<i>Wendy, my girlfriend</i>
<i>had a baby the other day.</i>

19:32.671 --> 19:34.631
<i>Uh, Santiago...</i>

19:35.507 --> 19:37.092
<i>named after her grandfather.</i>

19:39.136 --> 19:40.304
That's wonderful.

19:41.054 --> 19:43.182
It's a wonderful name, it's a very...

19:43.265 --> 19:44.850
It's a very strong name.

19:45.225 --> 19:47.102
It's different every time,

19:47.186 --> 19:50.522
but the feelings are still the same.

19:51.607 --> 19:54.818
I want a better life for them.
For all of them.

19:56.028 --> 19:57.321
<i>They can have that.</i>

19:58.780 --> 20:01.450
Well, you closed down
the new casino, Wendy.

20:05.454 --> 20:06.538
I have a plan.

20:06.622 --> 20:07.873
<i>Plan. Yeah.</i>

20:07.956 --> 20:10.876
<i>Well, your plan is bleeding my money</i>
<i>every day.</i>

20:14.838 --> 20:16.340
You've trusted me so far.

20:17.549 --> 20:18.842
<i>I don't trust you.</i>

20:19.968 --> 20:21.803
I trust my opinion of you.

20:23.347 --> 20:25.515
<i>So, please, the next time we talk,</i>

20:25.599 --> 20:28.060
<i>I want to hear that you closed this deal,</i>
<i>and, Wendy...</i>

20:30.062 --> 20:32.648
<i>Well, if you can't get what you want</i>
<i>with reason, then...</i>

20:32.731 --> 20:33.732
Yes.

20:33.815 --> 20:37.152
[inhales]
...you'll have to get it with force.

20:37.778 --> 20:38.695
[beeps]

20:38.779 --> 20:40.364
[call disconnects]

20:56.463 --> 20:58.882
There's half a million dollars
in the bag on the floor.

21:01.551 --> 21:03.804
It's yours if you leave town immediately.

21:13.480 --> 21:15.857
[unzips]

21:22.698 --> 21:25.200
All you people ever understand is money.

21:27.077 --> 21:28.287
Is that a yes?

21:31.206 --> 21:32.165
Come with me.

21:37.170 --> 21:38.130
No.

21:40.382 --> 21:41.300
Please.

21:47.180 --> 21:48.265
I can't.

22:04.156 --> 22:06.241
[whimpers] I can't. [panting]

22:15.208 --> 22:16.543
[Marty sighs]

22:20.339 --> 22:22.799
[Helen] <i>You don't ask this man</i>
<i>the same question twice.</i>

22:23.508 --> 22:25.761
Well, Helen, I'm not asking a question.
I'm telling you,

22:25.844 --> 22:27.846
as the person who directs these finances,

22:27.929 --> 22:30.724
we need to look for a short-term solution
for our laundering problems.

22:30.807 --> 22:34.895
And I am telling you, as his attorney,
my client wants his new business clean.

22:34.978 --> 22:36.688
You're gonna have to find another way.

22:36.772 --> 22:39.858
Tell me, is it your client's wish,
or is it Wendy's?

22:41.568 --> 22:42.527
Why would you ask that?

22:42.944 --> 22:46.782
Well, because I don't think you understand
how invested she is with your client.

22:46.865 --> 22:48.241
Meaning what, precisely?

22:56.333 --> 22:59.002
The only reason we can't move money
through the Missouri Belle now

22:59.086 --> 23:01.797
is because of an audit
that she brought down on us. Okay?

23:02.255 --> 23:04.174
-Maybe she should talk to Navarro.
-No.

23:04.383 --> 23:06.760
Her obsession with expansion,
it's fucked us.

23:06.843 --> 23:09.304
No, no, no, no. You fucked us, Marty.

23:09.930 --> 23:12.516
I've seen the warrant.
Wendy didn't cause this audit.

23:12.599 --> 23:14.851
You did, when you decided
to blow up a casino.

23:15.310 --> 23:17.187
Let's be plain. You played, you lost.

23:17.270 --> 23:19.523
I have no interest
in looking at that any further.

23:19.606 --> 23:21.525
My interest is in moving forward
as a team.

23:21.817 --> 23:23.902
Now, I assume
that's not gonna be a problem.

23:27.322 --> 23:29.116
-Is that gonna be a problem?
-No.

23:32.452 --> 23:34.538
You need to leave
before my daughter gets home.

23:42.212 --> 23:43.839
[footsteps approaching]

23:44.923 --> 23:46.133
[Carl] Mrs. Byrde.

23:48.718 --> 23:49.803
Mrs. Byrde.

23:49.970 --> 23:50.887
Oh.

23:51.596 --> 23:53.098
[laughing] I'm sorry.

23:54.433 --> 23:56.852
I was-- I was really lost there.
[chuckles]

23:57.269 --> 23:59.563
I quite often find myself as such.

24:02.482 --> 24:03.525
[Carl sighs]

24:06.945 --> 24:09.906
Thank you for coming out to see me.
I know our...

24:11.533 --> 24:13.493
our dealings have not been friendly.

24:14.119 --> 24:15.620
That's a way of putting it.

24:16.746 --> 24:18.915
But I have no desire to bankrupt you.

24:20.125 --> 24:21.334
How Christian.

24:21.460 --> 24:23.253
-Coffee, hon?
-Yes, please.

24:28.467 --> 24:31.428
-That's good. Thank you very much.
-Mm-hmm, sure. Oh, sure thing.

24:38.518 --> 24:40.061
What do you really want here?

24:42.772 --> 24:44.691
Some dignity would be nice.

24:46.651 --> 24:47.819
That's understandable.

24:48.904 --> 24:51.448
Because from what I see,
you don't get that at home.

24:55.952 --> 24:57.579
How long have you been married?

24:57.662 --> 24:59.873
[clears throat] Forty-four years.

25:04.669 --> 25:06.713
And for how many of those 44 years

25:06.796 --> 25:09.007
has she made you feel insignificant?

25:10.926 --> 25:12.260
[stammers] Now, look, I--

25:12.886 --> 25:14.221
I used to stay at home.

25:14.429 --> 25:15.347
I did.

25:15.931 --> 25:17.641
I raised the kids. I...

25:17.933 --> 25:21.311
I did the grocery shopping
and the driving and the cleaning,

25:21.394 --> 25:23.021
and it's a noble thing.

25:23.146 --> 25:24.856
It is, but it's...

25:26.024 --> 25:27.400
It's not what I wanted.

25:29.027 --> 25:29.986
So...

25:31.655 --> 25:32.822
I took back my life.

25:34.241 --> 25:36.409
And now I answer to only one person.

25:37.452 --> 25:38.370
Me.

25:41.540 --> 25:43.375
You sound like your husband.

25:45.919 --> 25:46.878
How's that?

25:48.046 --> 25:52.384
He told me my desires had taken
a backseat to my wife's for too long.

25:53.343 --> 25:55.470
He's the reason I pulled out of our deal.

25:58.598 --> 25:59.432
Huh.

26:00.267 --> 26:01.184
Well...

26:02.227 --> 26:04.771
My husband, he had a very good point.

26:07.440 --> 26:09.693
If you don't sell us your hotel,

26:11.444 --> 26:13.446
you're facing financial ruin.

26:13.822 --> 26:17.409
Now, you've got to get your wife
to do the right thing here.

26:17.492 --> 26:20.704
Otherwise, she's gonna lord this over you
your entire life.

26:21.288 --> 26:22.789
Is that what you want?

26:24.916 --> 26:26.293
-No.
-No.

26:27.794 --> 26:31.006
And even if this is all her fault,
do you think she'll ever see it that way?

26:33.633 --> 26:35.051
-No.
-No.

26:35.510 --> 26:37.804
So don't-- don't let that happen.

26:46.438 --> 26:48.857
I don't think I can win
this particular battle.

26:52.527 --> 26:56.281
For the rest of your life, Carl...

26:57.657 --> 27:00.619
every single day

27:00.994 --> 27:03.121
being told you're a failure?

27:04.873 --> 27:07.417
Now, you're a smart man.

27:08.043 --> 27:10.462
She might not be able to see that,
but I can.

27:11.755 --> 27:14.007
And if you can't get what you want
with reason,

27:14.090 --> 27:15.300
get it with force.

27:24.309 --> 27:25.894
[door closes]

27:36.029 --> 27:37.614
Talk to Wyatt lately?

27:38.448 --> 27:40.825
[sighs] I'm not doing this, Ruth.

27:40.909 --> 27:42.786
It's a simple fucking question.

27:43.703 --> 27:45.497
[clears throat] Yes.

27:45.747 --> 27:47.874
Are you gonna fucking tell me
how he's doing?

27:49.542 --> 27:52.128
You going to tell me what's going on
between you guys?

27:55.048 --> 27:57.008
Then I ain't telling you
how he's fucking doing.

27:58.301 --> 28:00.095
[vehicle approaching]

28:01.429 --> 28:02.514
[Ruth] Shit.

28:13.733 --> 28:15.485
What the fuck are you doing here?

28:16.152 --> 28:18.321
Always authentic. Hi.

28:21.950 --> 28:23.034
You okay?

28:23.702 --> 28:24.536
Yeah.

28:30.458 --> 28:33.336
I've been meaning to offer my condolences
about your father.

28:33.420 --> 28:34.879
Yeah? Is that right?

28:35.755 --> 28:37.757
I lost my dad when I was about your age.

28:39.467 --> 28:40.760
Was he murdered?

28:42.303 --> 28:43.888
-No.
-Hmm.

28:46.224 --> 28:48.017
What did your daddy do for a living?

28:48.560 --> 28:49.686
He was a surgeon.

28:51.229 --> 28:52.188
[scoffs]

28:53.398 --> 28:54.524
No, he wasn't.

28:56.651 --> 28:57.986
He fixed refrigerators.

28:58.653 --> 29:00.363
Died of a heart attack at 61.

29:00.447 --> 29:02.657
My mother, she was a teacher,

29:02.741 --> 29:05.326
and she is still alive
because she is too mean to die.

29:05.410 --> 29:06.536
What about your mom?

29:06.619 --> 29:07.787
She's dead.

29:07.871 --> 29:10.540
Oh, I'm very sorry to hear that.

29:10.623 --> 29:12.083
Yeah, it was a long time ago.

29:12.709 --> 29:14.169
We done enough chitchat now?

29:18.298 --> 29:20.759
Your contributions to the company
have been exceptional lately,

29:20.842 --> 29:22.302
and I wanted you to know that.

29:23.720 --> 29:24.763
Okay.

29:25.138 --> 29:26.514
Your slot machine idea,

29:27.098 --> 29:28.767
that really saved this last deal.

29:30.643 --> 29:31.519
All right.

29:31.644 --> 29:35.356
I'm impressed with your skills,
and I'm impressed with your loyalty.

29:36.065 --> 29:39.861
Now, because of this new casino,
Marty may have increased responsibilities.

29:41.446 --> 29:42.447
Like what?

29:43.072 --> 29:45.909
We want him to set up the books,
we'll need him on security.

29:45.992 --> 29:47.535
Startup concerns, generally.

29:49.037 --> 29:49.913
Okay.

29:50.955 --> 29:54.501
Could you run the day-to-day
at the Missouri Belle if Marty were away?

29:57.212 --> 29:58.546
Yeah, I could do that.

29:59.672 --> 30:01.174
That's what I was hoping.

30:04.552 --> 30:05.720
Have a lovely day.

30:13.102 --> 30:15.104
[engine starts]

30:18.149 --> 30:20.151
[vehicle pulls away]

30:30.787 --> 30:33.289
[shouting]

30:33.373 --> 30:34.541
[laughs]

30:34.624 --> 30:37.168
-[Jonah] Whoo!
-Whoo-hoo!

30:41.422 --> 30:42.674
[continues shouting]

30:42.757 --> 30:43.758
[horn honks]

30:43.842 --> 30:47.554
-Oh, fuck.
-[siren wails]

30:47.637 --> 30:50.682
Boat cops? That's a thing?

30:53.351 --> 30:54.853
Turn your engine off.

30:55.937 --> 30:58.231
Yeah, just... just let me do the talking.

30:58.731 --> 31:00.024
You're 14.

31:06.739 --> 31:08.575
Going a little fast there,
aren't you, bud?

31:09.450 --> 31:11.536
Hey, Sheriff Nix. It's Jonah Byrde.

31:11.619 --> 31:14.789
Oh, hey, Jonah.
I didn't recognize you there.

31:15.290 --> 31:17.125
So, who's this you're here with?

31:17.834 --> 31:19.252
This is my Uncle Ben.

31:20.044 --> 31:21.880
All right. All right, Uncle Ben.

31:21.963 --> 31:24.382
You wanna just slow it down
just a little bit for me there?

31:25.008 --> 31:25.925
We will.

31:27.135 --> 31:30.763
All right.
Say hey to your mom and dad for me, okay?

31:30.847 --> 31:32.056
-[Jonah] Okay.
-All right.

31:33.558 --> 31:37.020
-[police boat starts, retreats]
-What just happened here?

31:37.520 --> 31:39.272
I should probably drive us home.

31:43.860 --> 31:44.903
[engine starts]

31:46.571 --> 31:48.281
-[sighs]
-[engine revving]

31:48.781 --> 31:51.284
-[Ruth] Marty. Hey, Marty.
-Yes.

31:51.367 --> 31:53.953
-Are you fucking deaf?
-Well, you know, I'm busy, Ruth.

31:54.370 --> 31:57.165
That why you didn't tell me
that I was gonna have to run this place

31:57.248 --> 31:59.876
-while you get Big Muddy sorted out?
-What are you talking about?

32:00.001 --> 32:02.837
Helen came over to my place
to see if I can handle shit here

32:02.921 --> 32:04.923
because they're gonna need you over there.

32:08.134 --> 32:09.385
What did you tell her?

32:09.719 --> 32:12.180
That I could do it.
The fuck you think I told her?

32:14.390 --> 32:16.559
What? What?

32:16.643 --> 32:19.979
Uh, she's just--
she's exploring her options.

32:21.147 --> 32:23.274
Exploring her options for what?

32:23.816 --> 32:27.570
In case they decide to go
an unexpected way with me.

32:28.446 --> 32:29.364
It's okay.

32:32.325 --> 32:35.745
What-- What? How the fuck is it okay?

32:36.412 --> 32:37.705
You know, I should have known

32:37.789 --> 32:39.874
that giant fucking bitch
was up to something.

32:45.254 --> 32:46.589
What are we gonna do?

32:47.340 --> 32:49.634
I just gotta figure out a way
to keep on laundering.

32:50.593 --> 32:51.511
[beeps]

32:54.931 --> 32:58.309
[Carl] They will bankrupt us and for what?

32:58.851 --> 33:03.022
So we can be living out on the street,
but say that we won?

33:03.272 --> 33:06.359
[Anita] I don't understand
why you're not on my side on this.

33:06.442 --> 33:07.860
We gotta be reasonable here.

33:07.944 --> 33:10.989
These people have enough money
to ruin us five times over.

33:11.072 --> 33:12.991
What do you know about business?

33:13.616 --> 33:15.201
I'm putting my foot down.

33:18.246 --> 33:21.082
Oh. So, to me, you'll put your foot down.

33:21.791 --> 33:23.543
To me, you'll be the big burly man,

33:23.626 --> 33:27.296
but those two blonde b-words,
you barely have a thing to say.

33:31.134 --> 33:32.093
That's not fair.

33:32.719 --> 33:34.262
Don't talk to me about fair.

33:35.013 --> 33:37.557
[laughs] Is it fair I married the man

33:37.640 --> 33:40.476
with the worst business sense
in the state of Missouri?

33:41.936 --> 33:45.148
Everything everybody said about you
is right.

33:45.231 --> 33:48.359
You ran this place straight
into the ground.

33:48.693 --> 33:50.028
And you wanna know what else?

33:50.611 --> 33:52.196
I should have married your brother.

33:52.280 --> 33:54.449
-He was three inches taller than--
-Enough!

33:54.532 --> 33:55.992
[Anita shouts, body thuds]

34:33.613 --> 34:36.032
-[cell phone beeps]
-[line ringing]

34:39.035 --> 34:40.703
-[Marty] <i>Hello.</i>
-We got the hotel.

34:44.457 --> 34:46.417
Uh, that was fast.

34:47.126 --> 34:48.753
<i>They had a change of heart.</i>

34:50.922 --> 34:53.007
Okay. Uh, good. Um...

34:54.550 --> 34:57.887
Are you calling to offer me
some assistance here, Wendy?

34:59.555 --> 35:01.099
I'm just trying to keep you updated.

35:01.641 --> 35:03.851
<i>Got it. Okay, well, I'm updated,</i>

35:03.935 --> 35:05.645
and I'll talk to you later.

35:07.438 --> 35:08.397
[beeps]

35:19.534 --> 35:20.451
Hey, Mom.

35:23.621 --> 35:25.623
-Jonah.
-Yeah.

35:27.333 --> 35:29.669
I'm gonna get Zeke back from Mrs. Snell.

35:29.752 --> 35:31.170
[water runs]

35:32.046 --> 35:33.714
Are you sure that's a good idea?

35:35.341 --> 35:36.300
I am.

35:39.345 --> 35:40.263
Cool.

35:43.015 --> 35:44.684
Who's Zeke? A dog?

35:47.478 --> 35:48.521
[laughs] No.

35:51.482 --> 35:52.358
A baby.

35:52.900 --> 35:54.193
-Your baby?
-No.

35:55.862 --> 35:56.779
Huh!

35:57.947 --> 35:59.490
Gotta say...

36:01.242 --> 36:04.620
it's a complicated world
you got going down here, Wen.

36:04.704 --> 36:07.665
[inhales, sighs heavily]

36:08.207 --> 36:09.500
Casinos...

36:09.917 --> 36:10.918
babies.

36:11.294 --> 36:14.839
Your kid just talked his way
out of a speeding ticket on the lake.

36:15.464 --> 36:17.049
[stammers] Jonah was speeding?

36:17.133 --> 36:18.342
I was speeding.

36:20.344 --> 36:23.472
Oh, come on. He loved it.

36:23.764 --> 36:26.726
-He is by far my favorite.
-[laughs]

36:27.351 --> 36:29.478
He's a little boy version of you.

36:32.023 --> 36:33.941
God, no one has ever said that.

36:35.276 --> 36:36.152
So...

36:37.945 --> 36:38.779
[Wendy chuckles]

36:39.155 --> 36:40.406
...let me recount.

36:40.740 --> 36:42.533
-You had a baby.
-I didn't have a baby.

36:42.617 --> 36:44.619
You had a baby, moved to Missouri.

36:44.744 --> 36:46.245
You bought a casino...

36:46.746 --> 36:49.373
and apparently, the Ozark Boat Police,

36:49.457 --> 36:52.627
and then you bought another casino, and...

36:53.294 --> 36:56.672
you and Marty are doing really great.

37:03.554 --> 37:05.014
I didn't have a baby.

37:08.809 --> 37:10.686
Some bad money things...

37:11.562 --> 37:13.356
happened in Chicago, and...

37:15.024 --> 37:18.110
regardless of the--
of the money things, um...

37:20.321 --> 37:21.322
I had an affair.

37:23.282 --> 37:24.492
Everybody knows.

37:25.034 --> 37:26.244
Marty knows.

37:27.745 --> 37:29.080
[voice breaks] The kids...

37:30.122 --> 37:31.415
The kids know.

37:33.751 --> 37:37.255
And we moved here to start over.

37:38.172 --> 37:39.632
And it's been hard.

37:41.842 --> 37:44.804
We were fostering a baby for a while,
but whatever, it's, um...

37:51.519 --> 37:52.812
How was the affair?

37:53.437 --> 37:54.689
Fucking sucked.

37:57.733 --> 37:59.777
The end of it really fucking sucked.

38:02.530 --> 38:03.614
[Ben] Hmm.

38:05.449 --> 38:07.702
[sighs]

38:10.288 --> 38:11.580
Marty wants me to leave.

38:11.664 --> 38:13.374
Oh, he doesn't want you to leave.

38:13.874 --> 38:15.584
He told me to leave.

38:16.252 --> 38:18.629
Okay, well, yeah, he wants you to leave.

38:23.134 --> 38:25.594
-Who was the affair with?
-Just some guy.

38:47.825 --> 38:50.244
Aah! [sighs]

38:52.038 --> 38:54.290
-[laughing]
-So...

38:54.373 --> 38:55.708
[Ben laughs]

38:56.292 --> 38:58.294
[laughter continues]

38:59.587 --> 39:00.463
[pops]

39:02.631 --> 39:04.383
How are you gonna get this baby?

39:07.845 --> 39:10.264
I'm gonna pick a fistfight
with a hillbilly.

39:11.390 --> 39:12.767
-You're serious?
-Mm-hmm.

39:13.100 --> 39:14.602
What's Marty think about that?

39:15.394 --> 39:18.981
-I don't give a fuck what Marty thinks.
-Ooh.

39:19.565 --> 39:22.151
Look at you, Wendy Davis.

39:23.110 --> 39:24.403
Yes!

39:24.487 --> 39:26.489
[laughing]

39:30.368 --> 39:33.496
What I'm proposing is that
we lease you guys your equipment.

39:33.579 --> 39:37.166
I could make things smoother for you.
We could funnel everything through.

39:37.249 --> 39:41.003
One lender could pump some money back
into this local economy.

39:41.087 --> 39:42.671
Yeah, I don't know, man.

39:43.172 --> 39:46.133
Bands get nervous when you start
subbing out sound equipment, all right?

39:46.217 --> 39:47.468
-Do they? Um...
-Yeah.

39:48.344 --> 39:50.096
Well, um...

39:52.139 --> 39:53.933
Dickey, uh, would...

39:54.725 --> 39:57.937
would it mitigate any of those nerves
if-if we, uh...

39:59.647 --> 40:01.399
if we did an extra 100 grand?

40:03.150 --> 40:04.777
Will that make things better?

40:05.027 --> 40:07.154
Huh. That's, uh...

40:08.489 --> 40:09.573
That's reasonable.

40:09.990 --> 40:11.200
I would say so.

40:13.035 --> 40:15.413
-I'm gonna have to call the boys.
-Sure, of course.

40:15.496 --> 40:17.373
-Okay. Give me a minute here.
-Please do.

40:17.456 --> 40:19.166
And, um-- And if it's helpful, you know,

40:19.250 --> 40:21.961
same vendor could handle the merchandise
for you guys.

40:22.044 --> 40:25.131
If it's helpful. I just need
your signature on a few invoices

40:25.214 --> 40:27.049
-and a couple receipts.
-Hey, Kev. Yeah.

40:27.133 --> 40:29.552
Hey, um, so listen,

40:29.635 --> 40:31.846
the guy here wants us
to help him launder some money.

40:32.888 --> 40:34.390
[laughs] Yeah, man. An extra 100K.

40:35.599 --> 40:38.227
[laughing]

40:38.602 --> 40:39.979
Oh, look at you.

40:41.439 --> 40:43.524
Oh, your sock is almost off.

40:44.275 --> 40:47.236
You're silly. You're silly.

40:54.577 --> 40:56.370
Desperate for honey, Mrs. Byrde?

40:56.954 --> 40:58.205
I've got a proposition.

40:59.290 --> 41:00.583
Oh, hi, Mrs. Byrde.

41:02.835 --> 41:04.170
Hey, Wyatt.

41:05.045 --> 41:07.882
-I didn't realize you were working here.
-[Darlene] How can we help you?

41:09.133 --> 41:10.509
We've bought a new casino,

41:10.593 --> 41:13.888
and we're ready to cut you in,
in a very generous way.

41:13.971 --> 41:16.515
All you have to do is give up
your parental rights.

41:18.350 --> 41:19.852
What are you saying to me?

41:20.269 --> 41:22.605
I'm offering you money for Zeke.

41:22.688 --> 41:25.900
Hey, uh, I really don't think this is
the right place to be talking about this.

41:25.983 --> 41:29.069
Well, no,
he should have a nice young family.

41:29.153 --> 41:31.447
I mean, don't you agree, Wyatt?
Not an aging widow.

41:31.530 --> 41:34.533
-I think she's trying to upset you.
-Jacob would take the deal.

41:34.617 --> 41:37.161
I don't ever wanna hear you
utter his name again.

41:37.244 --> 41:38.621
We should all just calm down.

41:38.704 --> 41:41.248
I think we can all agree
that the child deserves better

41:41.332 --> 41:43.667
than a farm stand
and a redneck for a mama.

41:43.751 --> 41:44.668
[grunts]

41:50.090 --> 41:51.091
That ought to do it.

41:54.345 --> 41:55.930
-[Darlene] Get out of here!
-[Wyatt] Stop.

41:56.013 --> 41:58.516
-Get out of here before I kill you!
-Stop, Darlene.

41:59.725 --> 42:02.394
-She is gonna try and take my baby.
-She's not gonna take your--

42:02.478 --> 42:04.897
Listen, Darlene, she's not gonna
take your baby, I promise.

42:04.980 --> 42:05.940
I can't lose him.

42:06.857 --> 42:09.109
-I can't lose him.
-It's gonna be okay.

42:10.444 --> 42:12.530
-[Wyatt] Hey, buddy.
-[baby fussing]

42:12.613 --> 42:14.782
-I'm gonna kill her.
-No, you're not.

42:14.865 --> 42:16.617
We're gonna go home right now
so you can rest,

42:16.700 --> 42:18.494
and I'm gonna take care of Zeke, okay?

42:18.577 --> 42:19.578
-Okay?
-Yeah.

42:25.209 --> 42:26.710
[camera shutter clicking]

42:41.850 --> 42:43.811
Can I ask you a personal question?

42:45.437 --> 42:47.940
When did you start a 529 for your kids?

42:50.442 --> 42:52.027
When they started preschool.

42:54.363 --> 42:55.406
Okay, good.

42:56.323 --> 42:57.366
Thank you.

43:00.869 --> 43:05.708
I know Agent Evans has pressured you
to testify against the Navarro cartel.

43:07.835 --> 43:10.713
I get it. Textbook play.

43:10.796 --> 43:11.964
It's personal for him,

43:12.047 --> 43:14.800
just like everything was personal
for Agent Petty.

43:16.385 --> 43:17.344
But...

43:19.346 --> 43:21.890
there's a world
in which you don't testify...

43:23.350 --> 43:25.769
and you don't have to go
into witness protection.

43:28.355 --> 43:31.317
There's no one on my team
who can do what you do.

43:32.234 --> 43:34.320
You on the other side... [laughs]

43:36.238 --> 43:38.490
You offering me a job in the FBI?

43:39.199 --> 43:42.036
I'm saying if you pled guilty
to a separate offense...

43:43.495 --> 43:46.165
wire fraud, something casino related...

43:47.041 --> 43:51.128
you spend 18 months in a federal prison,
Navarro would know you didn't rat.

43:52.463 --> 43:53.380
Got it.

43:53.505 --> 43:56.592
Eighteen months, you'd be a free man.

43:58.677 --> 44:01.472
Provided you agree
to help me catch people like you.

44:03.098 --> 44:04.725
[sighs]

44:05.517 --> 44:07.561
You think I'm crazy, but I'm not.

44:08.729 --> 44:11.315
You'd be a contractor
for the federal government

44:11.398 --> 44:12.941
as a private citizen.

44:13.067 --> 44:14.818
It's a real possibility.

44:16.695 --> 44:21.659
Only the offer doesn't stand
if Agent Evans gets you first.

44:25.621 --> 44:26.705
Food for thought.

44:31.293 --> 44:32.252
[door shuts]

44:40.302 --> 44:41.470
[Evans] Yeah.

44:42.638 --> 44:44.139
Pretty clear, don't you think?

44:46.892 --> 44:49.687
And we got all five prints,
in case you were wondering.

44:51.355 --> 44:52.356
So...

44:54.024 --> 44:55.693
here's how this is gonna play out.

44:56.527 --> 44:57.695
We want Marty Byrde.

44:59.154 --> 45:03.158
We're sure he talked to your boss
in Kansas City about this job.

45:05.953 --> 45:07.246
If you help us get him,

45:08.247 --> 45:10.624
your friends don't have anything
to worry about.

45:13.335 --> 45:14.378
You don't...

45:18.298 --> 45:21.385
then you're all going to have problems.

45:25.431 --> 45:27.015
Do you understand?

45:31.729 --> 45:33.230
I'll do whatever you tell me.

45:36.024 --> 45:36.859
Good.

45:54.752 --> 45:55.878
What happened?

45:58.422 --> 45:59.882
You really want to know?

46:02.634 --> 46:03.844
Of course.

46:05.053 --> 46:06.221
I ran into a door.

46:17.608 --> 46:20.652
[bedroom door opens, shuts]

46:21.945 --> 46:22.863
[laughs]

46:40.422 --> 46:41.507
[door shuts]

46:48.472 --> 46:49.348
[Wendy] Hey.

46:50.933 --> 46:54.394
[Ben groaning]

46:59.149 --> 47:01.693
You got into your hillbilly fistfight.

47:03.278 --> 47:04.363
I did.

47:05.322 --> 47:06.782
I'm so proud of you.

47:06.865 --> 47:09.284
[laughing]

47:13.497 --> 47:14.456
Stay.

47:15.707 --> 47:17.167
What? No.

47:17.751 --> 47:19.795
I don't want it getting weird with Marty.

47:19.878 --> 47:21.046
No, you should stay.

47:22.548 --> 47:23.966
Why the change of heart?

47:27.344 --> 47:28.387
I want you around.

47:31.098 --> 47:32.015
Yeah?

47:33.767 --> 47:34.726
Yeah.

47:38.897 --> 47:39.982
[Ben] Oh.

47:41.984 --> 47:43.068
[sighs]

47:57.332 --> 47:58.584
I don't want you to burn.

48:02.337 --> 48:04.673
Don't worry.
I'll be gone before your friends get here.

48:05.549 --> 48:07.175
My friends are in Chicago.

48:09.636 --> 48:10.512
Okay.

48:12.848 --> 48:14.266
-[Erin] Any news?
-Hmm?

48:16.184 --> 48:17.686
On who beat up Dad?

48:19.146 --> 48:20.480
When I know, you'll know.

48:24.651 --> 48:25.694
Do I look okay?

48:29.573 --> 48:30.699
You look great.

48:32.075 --> 48:32.993
Okay.

48:33.452 --> 48:34.745
Call me if you need anything?

48:35.579 --> 48:36.455
I will.

48:40.626 --> 48:42.878
-I love you.
-Love you, too.

49:02.522 --> 49:04.524
[dialing]

49:16.411 --> 49:17.788
[line rings]

49:18.163 --> 49:20.791
[chimes]

49:24.920 --> 49:26.421
[line ringing]

49:30.676 --> 49:32.511
-[clicks]
-[Navarro] <i>Wendy Byrde.</i>

49:33.220 --> 49:35.055
[Wendy]
<i>I wasn't sure if I should call you.</i>

49:35.847 --> 49:37.391
[Navarro]<i> Oh, of course you should. </i>

49:39.226 --> 49:40.435
[Wendy] <i>We got the hotel.</i>

49:42.020 --> 49:45.107
[Navarro]<i> Good.</i> <i>I never doubted you.</i>

49:47.734 --> 49:50.654
[Wendy] <i>So, tell me...</i>

49:52.239 --> 49:53.365
<i>what can we do next?</i>

49:55.158 --> 49:57.577
<i>-Another hotel? Another casino?</i>
-[man mutters]

49:57.661 --> 50:00.163
<i>-Or if you have bigger plans, I--</i>
-[computer beeping]

50:04.418 --> 50:05.961
Hello, are you there?

50:06.128 --> 50:08.672
[Navarro] <i>Hang up.</i>
<i>This line is compromised.</i>

50:28.025 --> 50:29.568
[Jonah] What's the name of your school?

50:29.901 --> 50:30.944
[Erin] Woodlands.

50:32.821 --> 50:33.697
Cool.

50:35.615 --> 50:36.908
What's your middle name?

50:38.285 --> 50:39.202
Marie.

50:44.750 --> 50:47.377
Would you rather die
by a firing squad or drowning?

50:49.463 --> 50:51.673
Jonah, stop acting insane.

50:51.757 --> 50:54.468
[rock music playing on radio nearby]

50:54.551 --> 50:55.510
[man] Hey-hey!

50:57.262 --> 50:58.305
What's up, ladies?

50:59.806 --> 51:01.058
How's it going, little man?

51:02.350 --> 51:06.438
Hey, little thought.
Why don't you guys come over here?

51:07.314 --> 51:09.900
We got booze. We got views.

51:14.237 --> 51:15.614
Hey, Charlotte, right?

51:15.697 --> 51:16.698
[Charlotte] Yeah.

51:17.282 --> 51:18.408
[man] Nice tan.

51:19.868 --> 51:20.786
Come on.

51:22.704 --> 51:23.789
[man] Yeah!

51:31.713 --> 51:32.631
[man 2] All right!

51:32.756 --> 51:34.966
Would you mind staying
and watching our stuff?

51:36.885 --> 51:38.178
[man] Welcome aboard.

51:38.303 --> 51:40.639
-[Erin] Is this your dad's?
-[man] Oh, yeah, I borrowed it.

51:42.557 --> 51:43.809
All right, let's go.

51:46.186 --> 51:48.188
<i>♪ Cash rules everything around me ♪</i>

51:48.271 --> 51:51.358
<i>♪ C.R.E.A.M., get the money</i>
<i>Dollar dollar bill, y'all ♪</i>

51:51.441 --> 51:54.778
<i>♪ Cash rules everything around me</i>
<i>C.R.E.A.M., get the money ♪</i>

51:54.861 --> 51:56.321
<i>♪ Dollar dollar bill, y'all ♪</i>

51:56.404 --> 51:59.574
<i>♪ It's been 22 long, hard years</i>
<i>I'm still strugglin'... ♪</i>

51:59.658 --> 52:02.077
-[music continues over headphones]
<i>-</i>[Ben clears throat]

52:05.914 --> 52:07.082
Can I help you?

52:08.333 --> 52:10.961
[exhales]
Want me to save you a seat up there?

52:12.754 --> 52:14.131
I don't fucking think so.

52:17.342 --> 52:19.469
Then let me buy you dinner tomorrow night.

52:23.890 --> 52:24.808
Lunch?

52:26.268 --> 52:27.227
Breakfast?

52:29.020 --> 52:30.063
Snack?

52:31.815 --> 52:32.941
Glass of water?

52:34.317 --> 52:35.652
[laughing]

52:36.069 --> 52:37.529
Glass of water it is.

52:39.990 --> 52:40.907
Tomorrow.

52:49.040 --> 52:53.962
-[crowd cheering]
-[player strums electric guitar]

53:01.845 --> 53:04.472
Hello, Ozarks!

53:05.265 --> 53:07.809
Check yourselves out!

53:09.769 --> 53:13.273
Hey, are there any dentists
in the crowd tonight, by any chance?

53:13.940 --> 53:16.151
[playing "Time for Me to Fly"]

53:20.822 --> 53:26.745
<i>♪ I've been around for you</i>
<i>Been up and down for you</i> ♪

53:26.828 --> 53:29.873
<i>♪ But I just can't get any relief... ♪</i>

53:29.956 --> 53:31.333
Eighteen months?

53:34.628 --> 53:37.589
When you guarantee your service
to the FBI.

53:38.840 --> 53:42.344
<i>♪ But you still make me feel</i>
<i>Like a thief ♪</i>

53:44.054 --> 53:46.890
<i>♪ You got me peeling the years away... ♪</i>

53:46.973 --> 53:47.974
Okay, then.

53:49.893 --> 53:51.770
-Okay?
-Okay.

53:51.853 --> 53:55.774
<i>♪ I make you laugh</i>
<i>And you make me cry ♪</i>

53:57.192 --> 54:03.281
<i>-♪ I believe it's time for me to fly </i>♪
-[crowd cheering]

54:10.705 --> 54:13.208
<i>♪ You said we'd work it out ♪</i>

54:13.291 --> 54:16.378
<i>♪ You said that you had no doubt... ♪</i>

54:16.461 --> 54:18.838
[music fading out]

54:44.781 --> 54:49.119
[muted] <i>♪ I make you laugh</i>
<i>And you make me cry... ♪</i>

55:02.590 --> 55:04.592
<i>♪ It's time for me to fly... </i>♪

55:09.973 --> 55:12.976
All right, where the fuck are we going?
Where the fuck are we going?

55:13.059 --> 55:14.894
I don't need to fucking go in there.

55:14.978 --> 55:18.231
[music continues playing, muted]

55:18.857 --> 55:24.154
<i>♪ It's time for me to fly </i>♪

55:24.237 --> 55:26.239
<i>♪ It's time ♪</i>

55:34.622 --> 55:37.334
[band continues, vocalizing]

55:41.463 --> 55:43.465
[engine revving]

55:47.010 --> 55:50.597
[tires screech]

55:52.098 --> 55:54.100
<i>♪ Time for me to fly ♪</i>

55:54.184 --> 55:58.271
<i>♪ Baby, that's just how it's got to be ♪</i>

55:58.355 --> 56:02.150
<i>♪ Whoa, I know it hurts to say goodbye ♪</i>

56:02.233 --> 56:06.946
<i>♪ But it's time for me to fly ♪</i>

